latestPosts.caption:
✨Different types of eyeliner on a bare face ✨
Which one is your favourite?

I retook this video 2 times and this was my 3rd attempt. The first two times i hated how my under eyes looked because i had to keep wiping and reapplying and then I kept this video off to do it when my skin fully cleared. A realisation hit me that this is probably something that might make someone else feel confident and make myself confident in the process. Filmed it on a bare base and I’m loving it. My skin is healing beautifully and I’m so proud of myself for putting in the work for it ❤️✨

Used @maybelline tattoo eyeliner dip in for the one

latestPosts.caption:
Ever since I started the “Retro Malayalam” series I knew I had to do Manichitrathazhu because it’s my favourite movie ever. The thing is I knew I had to go all out with this and not just make do with whatever I had at home. So I rented the outfit,borrowed the jewellery, learned how to use a camera in one day, set up my make shift lights and created this 🖤
Although I can come no where close to the aesthetics and emotions in the movie I think this might be my best video yet.✨

Note : I’m not copying @shobana_danseuse maam and I did not even try to either because it would be like all the remakes of this movie, no where even close in comparison. I just borrowed the storyline and created my interpretation sitting in my room with limited resources (and no acting skills)

✨Presenting Nagavalli from Manichitrathazhu✨

Special thank you to the ones who gave me motivation and the resources to create this. Love you guys.

Audio Credits: @div.mp4 
Also check out @simerna.sushil Nagavalli look with a twist that she did for Halloween last year. It’s killer.

10 years of Chopstix Kakkanad. ❤️
Our second branch, the one that put us on the map.

I was just a kid when my dad dreamt of growing this brand beyond Palarivattom. Today, I’m old enough to witness that dream come to life and this branch has been such a big part of it.

From tech park lunch breaks to weekend family dinners, Kakkanad has become a favourite for so many of you, and for me, it’ll always be extra special.

Thank you for 10 years of love, loyalty, and unforgettable memories.
Here’s to the people, the food, and the stories that made it what it is. 🥢

latestPosts.caption:
Episode 4: You Made Me Buy It! 👀✨

This is an eyeliner and wing stamp duo designed to make winged liner super easy and it really delivers on that promise. The stamp simplifies the wing part, and the liner itself has a great formula: smooth, pigmented, and long-lasting.

The size of the pen gives you good control, which is great for steady lines. That said, I found it a little tricky to get a very thin liner on my first try, something to keep in mind if you prefer a more delicate look.
I wouldn’t necessarily say this is my favourite eyeliner or a must have product in your vanity, but if you’re someone who struggles to get equal sized wings this is great (you might have to touch it up a little according to your eyes)

Lately, I’ve made it a point to keep myself physically active and always on the move but let’s be real, the heat and sweat haven’t been kind to my skin 🥵 That’s why I’ve added a little Ayurvedic magic to my routine 💚
